description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you looking for an exciting Band 2 role in an inpatient unit? Would you like to work in our extraordinary forensic service to build a brighter and better future where you belong?  If so, perhaps this will be the opportunity for you.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ashford is a low secure forensic unit which provides specialist multi-disciplinary assessment for people with a learning disability, who also present with psychiatric disorder, personality disorder or challenging behaviour.  We are based at Tatchbury Mount in Calmore. Ashford Unit has recently had around £10 million of investment for a specially designed unit to be built. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role will offer an opportunity to offer career defining training and challenges; it will offer exposure to a very distinctive and rewarding environment, where you will be part of a close knit team.  You will work within a supportive multi-disciplinary where you will receive supervision from a Registered Nurse and be encouraged to progress your career within Southern Health. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We would welcome applications from HCSWs with experience of working with challenging behaviors; experience within a forensic environment is not essential, but a compassionate and caring nature is.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will work with other team members to to promote independence, by providing effective treatment and skills training within a risk management plan to enable the patient to be discharged in to the community, or where needs dictate, onto an appropriate continuing  healthcare service.  You should possess excellent team working skills, be patient focused and embracing of the Trust values.  You will have good communication skills and able to keep accurate and complete records.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ashford Unit operates a shift working pattern and there are a variety of shifts available.  We do aim to be as flexible as possible to ensure your working pattern helps with childcare/work/life balance and gives you plenty of free time to spend with family and friends, so please do feel free to discuss your preferences at interview.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the excellent NHS staff benefits; you will also be eligible to receive full Forensic Lead pay in addition to your normal basic salary.  This equates to an additional £1401.00 per year. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal discussion about the role prior to applying please contact &lt;strong&gt;Chris Davy, Clinical Ward Manager on 02382 310800&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Happy to Talk Flexible Working&lt;em&gt; - &lt;/em&gt;all&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;requests for flexible and part time working will be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
